<span id="freeTextContainer3389744173351681346"><b>3.5 Stars</b><br/><br/>I am definitely in the minority on this, but I just didn&apos;t <i>love </i> this one as much as most of my friends seemed to. <br/><br/>Don&apos;t get me wrong, it had a lot of really sweet elements and themes weaved throughout the story (e.g. the whole dandelion thing), and Archer and Bree were really cute (if somewhat flat?) characters, but it was just missing something for me. <br/><br/>Probably just me though.</span>
  <span id="freeText3389744173351681346" style="display:none"><b>3.5 Stars</b><br /><br />I am definitely in the minority on this, but I just didn't <i>love </i> this one as much as most of my friends seemed to. <br /><br />Don't get me wrong, it had a lot of really sweet elements and themes weaved throughout the story (e.g. the whole dandelion thing), and Archer and Bree were really cute (if somewhat flat?) characters, but it was just missing something for me. <br /><br />Probably just me though.</span>
