<div id="review_1957644807" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1957644807" />
    <a title="NMmomof4" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24665574-nmmomof4"><img alt="NMmomof4" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1515474309p2/24665574.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1957644807?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="NMmomof4" class="user" itemprop="url" name="NMmomof4" href="/user/show/24665574-nmmomof4">NMmomof4</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781538727379" href="/book/show/32822135-archer-s-voice">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=neighbors-live-with">neighbors-live-with</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=safe">safe</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=unlikely-couple">unlikely-couple</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=separation-without-other-partners">separation-without-other-partners</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=tears">tears</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=disordered-mc">disordered-mc</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=friends-to-lovers">friends-to-lovers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24665574-nmmomof4?shelf=5-star">5-star</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1957644807" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1633903054670821998"><b> 5 Stars <i>(Originally Read 2/1/2014)</i></b><br/><br/><b> 5 Stars <i>(Re-Read 4/3/2017)</i></b><br/><br/><b>Overall Opinion: </b> This is definitely one of my all time favorite books! The H, Archer, is the best! I think it would&apos;ve been easy to make his character into a beta male because of his life, but I LOVE how Ms. Sheridan made him have automatic alpha-male tendencies! It&apos;s not a huge secret that I&apos;m not big on beta males even when I feel for their trauma, so this was kind-of a huge deal for me in making me love his character! I also love </span>
  <span id="freeText1633903054670821998" style="display:none"><b> 5 Stars <i>(Originally Read 2/1/2014)</i></b><br /><br /><b> 5 Stars <i>(Re-Read 4/3/2017)</i></b><br /><br /><b>Overall Opinion: </b> This is definitely one of my all time favorite books! The H, Archer, is the best! I think it would've been easy to make his character into a beta male because of his life, but I LOVE how Ms. Sheridan made him have automatic alpha-male tendencies! It's not a huge secret that I'm not big on beta males even when I feel for their trauma, so this was kind-of a huge deal for me in making me love his character! I also love the stories where two damaged souls find peace and happiness in each other, and I think Ms. Sheridan is one of (if not <i>the</i>) best at creating these stories. If you've been living under a rock ;) and haven't checked out this book yet -- you need to meet you're new ultimate book boyfriend, Archer, ASAP!<br /><br /><b>Brief Summary of the Storyline: </b> This is Bree and Archer's story. Bree is on the run from her past, and ends up in a small town in Maine. She learns about the town mystery man by bumping into him one day, and is instantly drawn to him. After some awkward encounters, they form a friendship of sorts that eventually turns into more. Both of them carry a lot of baggage from their traumatic pasts that they have to work through, they have some sexy times, and they fall in love...and get a HEA ending.<br /><br /><b>POV:</b> This alternated between Bree (mostly) and Archer's POV.<br /><br /><b>Overall Pace of Story: </b> Good. I never skimmed and I thought it flowed well.<br /><br /><b>Instalove:</b> No, they take a while to develop stronger feelings.<br /><br /><b>H rating:</b> 5+ stars! I think he has to be one of my all time favorite Hs! He is so innocent, naive, and sweet -- BUT he also has an instinctive possessiveness and alpha-maleness (probably not a word)...so he becomes the best type of dichotomy to make the perfect bbf!<br /><br /><b>h rating:</b> 4 stars. Bree. I liked her. She was a super kind person at heart, and I love how she saw something in Asher and didn't give up.<br /><br /><b>Sadness level: </b>I didn't cry this go-round, but I remember crying the first time I read it.<br /><br /><b>Push/Pull:</b> Yes <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ The H is majorly weary of strangers/other people at first and pushes the h away. The H also leaves for a time. They both pursue the relationship at times.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Heat level:</b> Hot. They have some hot tension, chemistry, and scenes -- but not so much it takes away from the story.<br /><br /><b>Descriptive sex:</b> Yes<br /><br /><b>Safe sex:</b> Yes <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Mentions of birth control. I don't remember any mention of previous practices for the h, and the H was a virgin.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>OW/OM drama:</b> Yes <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ The H's cousin pursues the h and causes some drama. The h also has a long-time male friend that shows up that causes a little bit of drama. The H gets tricked into going to a strip bar and ends up in a private room with a stripper that gives him a lap dance. He knew her from when he was younger and crushed on her. She makes him touch her breasts and I believe it is implied he orgasms. This is after feelings have developed between the h and H. While I didn't consider this cheating because I feel like he was tricked and it was a unique situation, I understand that some readers might consider it so. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Sex scene with OW or OM:</b> No<br /><br /><b>Cheating: </b>No<br /><br /><b>Separation:</b> Yes <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[They are separated for ~3 months, and there was mention that neither of them had other partners during this time.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Possible Triggers: </b>Yes <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Violence/murder/domestic violence/alcoholism/cheating (side characters - off page through memories), loss of parents (off page), H has damaged vocal cords and cannot talk, virgin H, and violence (on page).  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Closure: </b> It had great closure with a jump ahead epilogue and a HEA ending.<br /><br /><b>How I got it:</b> I paid $3.99 for it on Amazon back in 2014.<br /><br /><b>Safety:</b> This one should be <u>Safe</u> for most safety gang readers<br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[<br />- <b>Does Not</b> have cheating<br />- <b>Does Not</b> have a descriptive sex scene with OW/OM<br />- <b> Does</b> have the H pushing the h away<br />- <b> Does</b> have a ~3 week separation between the h and H<br />- <b> Does Not</b> have abuse<br />- <b> Does Not</b> have OTT sad parts<br />- <b>Does </b> have a HEA ending <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
  <a data-text-id="1633903054670821998" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

